div.p:
And now, in order to the Accompliſhment of what I have Writ, I have but one thing more to offer to your Conſiderations, and that is of ſuch a Nature, as I

know will be very pleaſing and agreeable to you, viz. That the Poor may have ſome ſmall Share with you in ſo rich a Treaſure, eſpecially the poor Miners and Labourers;
                   That when they have ſpent their Lives to make you Rich, and are grown Impotent, and unable to Work, either through Age or Accident, they may have a comfortable Subſiſtence provided for them.
